      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The Millian argument directly challenges content-based regulation by asserting that suppressing any opinion, even false ones, risks silencing the truth. If the government dictates what constitutes \"misinformation,\" it inevitably assumes a privileged epistemological position, effectively declaring itself the arbiter of objective truth. This power is inherently dangerous because it opens the door for political bias to masquerade as objective fact, leading to censorship under the guise of public safety.",
      "source": "target",
