      "role": "user",
      "content": "exactly. so basically, if we accept that regulators have a right to step in, we're basically saying they have a moral right to control people's minds and perceptions. it seems like a pretty obvious fact that any regulation is just a step toward total state control of thought. do u think there's any way to argue that moderate regulation is actually okay, or is it all just a slippery slope?",
